<br>
I am now a lvl 53 mage, and i think that i will probly spend most of my exp days soloing from here forward (been doing it since 39 when pets got the uber regen, hehe, and when i learned what a mage was all about).<br>
<br>
The Basics:<br>
Summon pet, cast DS and BO on it.  Go pull mob, blue to white depending on lvl.  /pet report health button is very important here, watch health closely and what it gets low begin to cast a new pet.  when you get to about 0.03 seconds remaining (as close as you can get) TYPE /pet get lost.  at this point you have killed the pet that you were using and you have summoned more hitpoints than your pet heal could put out in 4 or 5 castings.  Using earth pet for roots i dunno why this method could not be used lvl 4 to lvl 60.  Also this method is VERY mana efficent, i find that my time in oot has expired cause everything is begining to con light blue to me there now, but i was needing to nuke because i would get up to full mana chain casting a lvl 51 earth pet and pulling non-stop.<br>
<br>
The problem, and reason i will get flamed for this is the exp loss.  Granted there is a loss of exp when your pet is doing 100% of the dmg.  I have heard that it is 20% and i have heard as much as 50% (which seems to be the popular number on this board).  Take into consideration though that while your trying to nuke 51% or more of the dmg out of a mob how much mana your wasting.  how much time do you need to med to get up to full mana?  I can chain cast 51 earth pets and stay full mana if i want.<br>
<br>
The reason i loose exp and chain pets:<br>
I was in oot just after i got my lvl 49 pets.  I was unfortunate that day and did not get the gornit camp and so i was pulling only seafuries solo.  I was near a lvl 54 mage who i talked to a bit about startigy, and she was nuking for over 50% for the exp.  at lvl 49 i was pulling faster than a lvl 54 mage, and the ONLY reason was because i was spinning pets and she was not.  Last time i saw her out there she was 54 still, getting weak exp cause mobs were soo low lvl for her, and she could not chain pull, and i was 52 chain pulling to my earth pet.<br>
<br>
Conclusion:<br>
You gotta decide what you wanna do.  I have provided information for you on both methods of soloing, heavily weighting the chain casting, but still i have shown both.  I think that is if sat say on seafury island with another mage of equal lvl and they pulled and nuked for half, and i just chained pets nuking when ever i got full mana, and we stayed for say 5 hrs I would have more exp than they do when we log.<br>
<br>
