</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unitrooftheorb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nitro of the Orb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#333333>(5/7/02 11:01:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Necros vs. Mages</span><hr size=1> Well, I had a really long essay on this. But of course, I hit some hotkey and everything was automatically deleted. /sigh. The main complaint I have with necros is the spell line Screaming Terror. (i think its a spell line, may be a single spell). It's a necro Mez... they shouldn't get it. Plain and simple. It's overpowering, they already are one of the best classes in the game. A weakness to fear kiting is that adds are hard to deal with. With mez, its easy. Take it out, VI. Let the Necros bitch. Such a hard life they have, eh?<br>
<br>
Necros, for the most part, CANNOT solo better in the following situations<br>
<br>
A) high MR MoBs (best example is felwithe... the guards there are hard-hitting, high MR mobs. genuinely hard. Malosi takes care of the resits for the most part. Necro's don't get it... and they get chewed through by high MR things. Pets can NOT tank.)<br>
<br>
B) Dungeon mobs that hit hard. With the exception of undead dungeons (best example being lguk undead side) necros can't take any dungeon mobs that hit even remotely hard. They cannot dish out very high, very fast damage to compensate for the MoB damage, and the pets cannot tank.<br>
<br>
Anyone who says this is a small list should take a look... This, for the most part, would encompass a lot of area. I do not doubt that Necros, outdoors, in a wide open area with a single MoB and no potential for adds, could solo very well. Better than me, most likely. But a lot of MoBs necro's cannot handle. For the guy who said, and I quote, &quot;For those who said Necros are about even to Mages in soloing... They're not even in the same ballpark.&quot;<br>
<br>
That's just blatantly false. Both excell in their own areas. You're bragging because you think your class is better. It's the classic &quot;my dad could beat up your dad&quot; three year old complex. Not meant to be an insult of course, but it is. <br>
<br>
Looks like I rewrote my essay, somewhat. I do NOT think that fear is overpowering. I believe it is part of the Necro class, fits into their role, and is a good skill. It's not omni-useful. In fact, its probably not as useful as most people think. <br>
<br>
One last point: Damage Shields. Mage DSes are an excellent source of damage. Unfortunately I didn't do my homework, but to my knowledge, Necros do not get any damage shields. Think about it... level 49 DS Shield of Lava. Manaless from our quest robe. 25 damage returned per hit. Let's say you're fighting a monster hitting 4 times per round, and 20 rounds elapse before the end of the battle. Assuming the MoB hit every time, that's 2000 free damage. *shrug* just my thoughts.<br>
<br>
Summary: Necros are NOT all-powerful compared to mages. Depending on the situation, both classes are very powerful. But get rid of Necro mez VI... it doesn't fit. It's just an overpowering spell that doesn't fit the class.<br>
<br>
Just my 2c,<br>
Draogan Darksight<br>
52nd Mage of The Seventh Hammer<br>
